The paper deals with steganography, which involves hiding information within other data. This is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with codes and their efficiency in embedding data. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely, as steganography is often used in conjunction with cryptography to hide messages. 

cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possibility, as steganography is often used in multimedia files such as images and videos. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility, as steganography can be used to hide information within images. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility, as the paper evaluates and compares the performance of different steganographic methods, which could involve machine learning techniques.
